msContents.summary: Lecture notes, primarily on Aristotle's works but also on the Sphaera mundi of Johannes de Sacro Bosco, written by Petrus S. Langevelt at Louvain, Belgium.

msItem.title: Commentarius in universam Aristotelis Physicam, f. 3r (V.2)
Commentarius in Spheram Joannis de Sacrobosco, f. 110r (V.2)

supportDesc.extent: 2 volumes (293, 383 leaves) : volume 1: 199 x 156 (170 x 120) mm. bound to 211 x 167 mm. ; volume 2: 198 x 157 (172 x 120) mm. bound to 209 x 165 mm
supportDesc.foliation: v.1, paper, 293; [1-293]; v.2, paper, 383; [1-383]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by one hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: Engraved title pages, v. 2, f. 3 signed Pet. Rucholle fec., f. 137 Q. Boel fec., I.G. exc.; a few schematic drawings in v. 2; two engravings bound in v. 2.

origin.p: Written in Louvain, from 1646 (v.1, f. 2r) to 1648 (v.2, f. 243r).
